# Task workflow

Use this when the user assigns work. Pair with **`project-context.mdc`** and the deploy/verify rules in `.cursor/rules/`.

## Planning vs execution

- **Planning and architecture** — reason in this session; split large work into clear steps.
- **Implementation** — prefer direct edits for normal/low tasks; use **parallel subagents** (or focused exploration) for independent chunks of high-priority work. Prompts should be literal: paths, intent, acceptance checks.
- **Low-priority** (typos, one-liners) — do inline without extra orchestration.

## Step 1 — Triage

Classify tasks:

| Priority | Criteria | Examples |
|----------|----------|---------|
| **High** | Architecture, multi-file refactors, 3+ files, deep bugs | New system, data rework, complex UI flow |
| **Normal** | 1–2 files, straightforward fixes, new screen/component | Button, crash fix, prompt tweak |
| **Low** | Cosmetic, copy, tiny cleanup | Typo, padding |

Present a short checklist before starting:

```markdown
## Task Plan
### High — [ ] …
### Normal — [ ] …
### Low — [ ] …
```

## Step 2 — Execute

- **High first** — subdivide by layer (data / VM / UI). Parallelize only where dependencies allow.
- **Normal next** — sequential unless independent.
- **Low last** — quick passes.

Optional: read **`skills-and-tools.mdc`** for Superpowers / frontend-design / debugging skills when the task fits.

## Step 3 — Checklist updates

Mark items done as you finish; end with a short summary of what changed.

## Step 4 — Tests

After substantive changes:

```bash
gradle test
```

If failures: diagnose (your change vs pre-existing). Fix code or update tests to match intended behavior — **do not delete tests** to green. Add regression tests for logic bugs. Retry up to ~3 cycles; then stop and report.

See **`testing.mdc`** for what to test by change type.

## Step 5 — Deploy and verify

Follow **`build-deploy.mdc`**, **`debug-bridge-verify.mdc`**, and **`debug-bridge-test-procedures.mdc`** (minimum **P0–P1** after app changes; add contextual procedures). **`shell-permissions.mdc`** for non-`sudo` commands.

Do not claim runtime verification from compile/tests alone when app sources or app Gradle changed.

## Step 6 — Finish

Confirm tests + deploy/verification (when required) before saying work is complete. If the user asked to commit, follow **`commit-after-verify.mdc`**.

## Step 7 — README

Update **`README.md`** only when user-visible structure, game systems, build requirements, or stack changed — not for internal refactors invisible to readers.
